The paper proposes an approach for case adaptation in a case-based reasoning system using qualitative algebras as knowledge representation languages. This involves applying a substitution and then repairing potential inconsistencies through belief revision. This approach is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), computational complexity (cs.CC), databases (cs.DB), and programming languages (cs.PL).
